title: Appointments to Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
	The Government announced today (November 27) the re-appointment of the 
	incumbent Chairman of the Hospital Authority, Professor John Leong Chi-yan, 
	and two serving members, Mr Andrew Fung Hau-chung and Mr Stephen Lee 
	Hoi-yin. Mr Ivan Sze Wing-hang, Mr Jason Yeung Chi-wai and Ms Priscilla Wong 
	Pui-sze are appointed as new members to the Hospital Authority. All the

Pui-sze are appointed as new members to the Hospital Authority. All the 
	appointments are for a term of two years with effect from December 1, 2015. Following are the brief biographies of the three new members: Mr Sze is the Director of a real estate development company. He serves on 
	the Tung Wah Group of Hospitals Advisory Board and the Standing Committee on 
	Directorate Salaries and Conditions of Service, as well as the Medical 
	Sub-group of the Steering Committee on Strategic Review on Healthcare

Sub-group of the Steering Committee on Strategic Review on Healthcare 
	Manpower Planning and Professional Development. Mr Yeung is a retired banker. He is a member of the Steering Committee on 
	Review of Hospital Authority and the Insurance Advisory Committee, as well 
	as the Board of Directors of the Financial Dispute Resolution Centre. Ms Wong is a practising barrister. She is the Chairman of the Employees 
	Compensation Assistance Fund Board, as well as a member of the Financial 
	Reporting Review Panel, the Joint Committee on Student Finance and the Panel

Reporting Review Panel, the Joint Committee on Student Finance and the Panel 
	of the Witness Protection Review Board. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed Mr Sze, Mr Yeung 
	and Ms Wong to the Hospital Authority. He also thanked Mr Cheng Yan-kee, Mr 
	Patrick Ma Ching-hang and Mrs Margaret Leung Ko May-yee, who will retire 
	from the Hospital Authority with effect from December 1, 2015, for their

from the Hospital Authority with effect from December 1, 2015, for their advice and contribution to the Hospital Authority over the years. The Hospital Authority, as from December 1, 2015, will comprise a chairman, 23 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority.
